The paper discusses the application of Bayesian Convolutional Neural Networks using Variational Inference to tasks like Image Classification, Image Super-Resolution, and Generative Adversarial Networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of probability distributions over weights, which is a common topic in sub-categories like cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
